<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-2197] Document default property value support</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2197</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As Spring and some other libraries, it would be nice to support default property value. For sample :&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;${sys:property_name:default_value&lt;/tt&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lookup will return the actual system property value of &quot;property_name&quot; if defined, otherwise &quot;default_value&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The form without default value would work as normal and return a &quot;null&quot; value when this property is not defined.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The way of getting the default value will be similar to &quot;ResourceBundleLookup&quot; and both &quot;EnvironmentLookup&quot; and &quot;SystemPropertiesLookup&quot; will benefit this feature.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch incoming...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
